      "label": "strategy_expert",
      "instructions": "Develop an optimization algorithm to identify the locations of hidden polyominoes. Given the shapes and the ability to perform single-cell queries or multi-cell noisy aggregate queries, design a strategy that minimizes total probing cost. Consider using a probabilistic approach or a greedy search to find high-probability oil cells while accounting for the noise parameter. The goal is to decide which coordinates to query next to maximize information gain per unit cost."
    },
    {
      "label": "implementation_expert",
      "instructions": "Implement the interactive loop in Python. Create a robust system to read the initial grid and polyomino data from stdin, manage the current state of the grid and known oil cells, and handle the communication protocol. This includes writing the q command for queries and the a command for the final submission to stdout, ensuring all outputs are flushed immediately. The implementation must strictly follow the input/output contract and handle the tester's responses correctly."
    }
  ],
  "synthesis_brief": "The parent agent will integrate the strategy_expert's decision-making logic (which coordinates to query) into the implementation_expert's interactive loop. The final main.py will use the strategy to drive the queries and the implementation framework to communicate with the tester and submit the final answer."
}
